two young men and two young women who 
apparently were inhaling laughing gas to get high were found dead 
monday in a storeroom of a building housing a dental clinic 
authorities said 
the bodies were found shortly before noon in a small room near 
an empty tank of nitrous oxide a gas used by dentists as an 
anesthetic iron county prosecutor scott burns 
its believed that they were inhaling the gas he said 
burns said there was no sign of forced entry 
he identified the victims as owen marc gregerson 18 and shawn 
williams 19 both of cedar city christine cherie miller 20 of 
fillmore and margaret j probert 20 of scipio 
