<TEXT>
the media generalassociated press poll on civil 
rights was based on telephone interviews june 22july 2 with 1223 
adults in the continental united states 
phone numbers were selected randomly by computer and interviews 
were conducted with the adult at each household who had the most 
recent birthday 
the results were weighted to adjust for variations in the 
sample the poll has a 3point margin of error meaning that if 
every adult american were asked the same questions the results 
theoretically would be within 3 points of the polls results 19 
times out of 20 the error margin is larger for subgroups 9 
points for example for blacks who made up 11 percent of the 
adjusted sample their share of the adult population 
there are other sources of potential error in polls including 
the wording and order of questions these are the questions and 
responses in this poll because of rounding some totals may exceed 
100 
1 overall do you think blacks and other minorities have the 
same opportunities as whites in the united states or not 
yes 54 percent no 42 percent dont know or no answer 4 
percent 
2 in the past 25 years do you think the country has moved 
closer to equal opportunity among the races or farther away from 
it or has there been no movement 
closer 84 percent farther 5 percent no movement 7 percent 
dkna 4 percent 
3 do you think it is possible to achieve equal opportunity 
among the races in the united states or not 
yes 71 percent no 24 percent dkna 5 percent 
3a if yes do you think it will happen in your lifetime or not 
yes 53 percent no 40 percent dkna 7 percent 
4 do you think blacks and other minorities should receive 
preference in hiring to make up for past inequalities or not 
yes 15 percent no 79 percent dkna 6 percent 
5 do you think blacks and other minorities should receive 
preference in college admissions to make up for past inequalities 
or not 
yes 18 percent no 76 percent dkna 5 percent 
6 do you think blacks and other minorities receive equal 
treatment as whites in the criminal justice system or not 
yes 43 percent no 43 percent dkna 15 percent 
6a if no do you think blacks and other minorities are denied 
justice because of their race or not 
yes 69 percent no 24 percent dkna 7 percent 
7 do you think jesse jacksons campaign for the democratic 
presidential nomination advanced the cause of civil rights set 
back the cause of civil rights or had no effect on it 
advanced 51 percent set back 7 percent no effect 33 
percent dkna 9 percent 
8 do you have any close friends who are black or not 
among whites yes 67 percent no 31 percent dkna 2 percent 
9 do you have any close friends who are white or not 
among blacks yes 94 percent no 5 percent dkna 2 percent 
10 do you think american society overall is racist or not 
yes 55 percent no 37 percent dkna 9 percent 
