vice president george bush who landed in new orleans this morning 
for an appearance at gop platform sessions said phillips bush 
also planned a stop at the superdome site of the convention 
right now new orleans is mostly getting the weaker western 
side of the storm the folks that have been getting the worst of it 
are those south of new orleans said meteorologist mike koziara 
meanwhile alberto the seasons first named storm fizzled out 
today off the canadian coast zimmer said 
its lost its tropical characteristics he said now its 
just a storm the center will no longer issue bulletins on it he 
said 
shortly after noon sunday the forecasters had issued a tropical 
storm warning for maines coast from bar harbor to eastport but 
they canceled it less than six hours later 
the storm was most likely to make landfall at yarmouth halifax 
or eddy point nova scotia forecasters said 
typically there are 10 named storms during the sixmonth 
hurricane season which begins june 1 last year there were only 
three hurricanes and four tropical storms in the atlantic 
