agencys european field office at rheinmain air base in west 
germany and his deputy us army lt col scott g lang 
under the ussoviet accord the united states and the soviet 
union will remove all groundlaunched nuclear missiles with a range 
of between 300 and 3400 miles 
the treaty which removes an entire class of nuclear arms said 
lyebedev marks the beginning of an unprecedented stage in the 
