<TEXT>
george p shultz joined the reagan 
administration in 1982 and combined with previous tasks during his 
service to president nixon he has spent 11 years as a cabinet 
officer sixth on the alltime list 
during his tenure as secretary of state shultz has flown over 1 
million miles to more than 70 countries and it was on a visit to 
bolivia on monday that he had his closest brush with danger 
a bomb exploded as his motorcade was making its way from the 
airport to downtown la paz but shultz and other members of his 
party escaped injury 
when alexander m haig jr resigned unexpectedly as secretary in 
june 1982 president reagan was intent on finding a replacement who 
could win swift senate confirmation 
reagan settled quickly on shultz whose appointment was greeted 
with bipartisan praise he assumed his duties less than a month 
later becoming the first official in us history to serve in four 
cabinetlevel posts state treasury labor and the office of 
management and budget 
shultzs most significant achievement has been was a treaty with 
the soviet union to abolish all us and soviet intermediaterange 
nuclear missiles his biggest disappointments thus far have been 
the administrations inability to bring about peace and democracy 
in nicaragua and to promote arabisraeli peace negotiations 
but shultz cannot be faulted for lack of effort he has made 
four trips to the middle east this year and on wednesday he will 
make his third trip to central america in five weeks 
shultz became secretary of state after serving as president of 
the bechtel group an international construction and engineering 
firm where his annual income was estimated at 500000 to 1 
million 
to many shultz looks and sounds like an economics professor on 
leave from stanford university which he is 
theyve established a chair in my honor he frequently 
remarks i told them when im through with this job ill need a 
couch 
