independence by next june 1 if cuba leaves angola by that date 
bothas announcement monday suggested the two sides were close 
to agreeing on a common date 
south africa would grant namibia its independence under terms of 
un resolution 435 which the security council passed in 1978 and 
which calls for unsupervised elections botha said 
the united nations in 1966 revoked south africas mandate over 
namibia a huge but sparsely populated land of 13 million people 
swapo which has bases in southern angola would be the clear 
favorite to win independence elections in namibia 
issues that would still have to be resolved include 
the future of unita 
african national congress bases in angola south africa says 
