<TEXT>
javier perez de cuellar is mild of manner 
and would not boast of his diplomatic skill but he had reason for 
pride monday when he announced a ceasefire in the persian gulf war 
the iraniraq war is the latest in several seemingly intractable 
conflicts for which the united nations has been asked to help find 
a solution 
the soviet union is withdrawing its estimated 115000 soldiers 
from a 10yearold civil war in afghanistan under a unmediated 
agreement signed april 14 
combatants in cambodia southwestern africa and the western 
sahara have asked the world organization to find ways of ending 
their wars without a defeat for any party 
perez de cuellars diplomatic successes in afghanistan and the 
gulf contrast with his early disappointment in the 74day falkland 
islands war between argentina and britain it was fought in 1982 
the year after he became un chief executive 
the softspoken diplomat from peru now 68 is known for 
discretion and diligence he likes to quote the french aphorism 
le ton fait la chanson which means the melody makes the song 
not a loud voice 
the secretarygeneral tried to create harmony between britain 
and argentina as londons fleet of warships steamed toward the 
falklands but both sides hardened their positions after two weeks 
of talks argentina also claims the islands which it calls the 
malvinas 
before the falklands conflict ended israel invaded lebanon the 
israelis defied security council demands for a ceasefire and 
withdrawal and bypassed the 7000member un peacekeeping force 
in southern lebanon 
with infinite patience perez de cuellar insists it is much 
easier for a government to make concessions to the united nations 
than to make concessions to one another or to a big power 
that theory bore fruit in the past week when iraq abandoned its 
demand for direct talks with iran as a first step toward peace 
accepting perez de cuellars compromise suggestion for direct talks 
immediately after a ceasefire takes effect 
he announced monday that the truce would begin aug 20 and the 
peace talks aug 25 
after he became secretarygeneral perez de cuellar said he 
would not seek a second fiveyear term because the un chief must 
remain independent and not curry favor with the five permanent 
security council members he relented however and was reelected 
in 1986 with no serious opposition 
a career diplomat he was perus ambassador to the united 
nations from 197175 and served on the security council in 197374 
he was un special representative to cyprus in 197577 and in 
1979 was appointed undersecretarygeneral for political affairs 
he held that post until becoming secretarygeneral and also was 
special representative to afghanistan in 1981 
