that simulate the tide 
us soil conservations service researchers hope the smooth 
cutgrass giant cutgrass and gulf cord grass will prevent the 
coastal erosion that takes some 32000 acres a year of louisianas 
32 million acres of coastal wetlands 
a tough reedy carpet of such marsh grass can form a natural 
barrier against tides waves wind and the effects of dredging 
