<TEXT>
interco inc on monday rejected as inadequate a 
sweetened 268 billion buyout offer from a washingtonbased 
investor group and took moves to strengthen its defenses against 
an unwanted takeover 
the manufacturer and retailer of apparel and furniture stated 
that in addition to rejecting the 70 a share merger proposal 
offered earlier monday by city capital associates its board of 
directors approved a plan to sell the companys apparel division 
which accounts for nearly a fourth of its sales 
the interco board concluded that the interests of the 
companys shareholders were better served by the companys 
continued pursuit of the restructuring of the company which is 
presently under consideration the company said 
interco stock which rose by more than 13 a share when the 
groups initial offer of 64 a share was announced july 28 rose 
412 to 7250 a share on the new york stock exchange 
the interco board also amended its poison pill defense 
against hostile takeover so that it takes effect if a suitor 
acquires 15 percent or more of intercos 384 million outstanding 
common shares 
the company said the change was aimed at preventing an 
openmarket stock accumulation program following the announcement 
of a proposal to acquire interco or a street sweep that could 
accompany or follow a tender offer for the company in which all 
interco shareholders would not participate equally and at a fair 
price 
city capital owns 87 percent or 314 million of intercos 
outstanding common shares 
when it made its initial 64 a share offer valued at about 
246 billion city capital said it might increase its bid based on 
further review of information about interco 
the company had sales of 334 billion last year with the 
apparel group contributing about 24 percent 
interco manufactures mens and womens apparel footwear 
furniture and home furnishings some of its brand names are among 
the best known in the united states including london fog clothing 
florsheim and converse shoes and broyhill and ethan allen 
furniture 
in addition to its manufacturing operations interco operates 
201 retail locations in 15 states including homeimprovement 
centers general merchandise discount stores mens specialty 
apparel shops and specialty department stores 
</TEXT>
